# Quartermaster SOP

[bold]1.[/bold] In the event of a major crisis, such as terrorism, expediency is to be favored over paperwork, as excessive bureaucracy may be detrimental to the well-being of the station;

[bold]2.[/bold] The Quartermaster is [bold]not[/bold] permitted to authorize the ordering of [color=#cb0000]Security[/color] equipment and/or gear without express permission from the [color=#cb0000]Head of Security[/color] and/or [color=#1b67a5]Captain[/color]. An exception is made during station ending emergencies or terrorism, where said equipment is to be delivered to [color=#cb0000]Security[/color], post-haste;

[bold]3.[/bold] The Quartermaster is required to follow the guidelines put in place for [color=#b18644]Cargo Technicians[/color];
